og</title><link>https://imgur.com/gallery/9eNJx94</link><description><![CDATA[<div><img alt="" src="https://i.imgur.com/ogEpNAQ.gif" style="max-width: 90%; height: auto;"></div><div><span></span></div></div>]]></description><guid>https://imgur.com/a/9eNJx94</guid><dc:creator><![CDATA[Devi8tor]]></dc:creator></item><item><title>Its a loveless cashgrab like so many others.</title><link>https://imgur.com/gallery/74aMfJL</link><description><![CDATA[<div><img alt="" src="https://i.imgur.com/8Y9OWVR.png" style="max-width: 90%; height: auto;"></div><div><span></span></div><div>Lets be real, it will be bad for the same reason wheel of time is bad: No love for the original material, just trying to make it the next Game of Thrones! 
All they care about is the Lord of the Rings name and nothing beyond that. 
If the show is at least decent, I would be very suprised.

And they will use the "Its because of racism" argument once the show flopps. Because thats the main defense lately...</div></div>]]></description><guid>https://imgur.com/a/74aMfJL</guid><dc:creator><![CDATA[Raoul9753]]></dc:creator></item><item><title>Opps</title><link>https://imgur.com/gallery/bI2MvaE</link><description><![CDATA[<div><img alt="" src="https://i.imgur.com/otQagmq.jpg" style="max-width: 90%; height: auto;"></div><div><span></span></div></div>]]></description><guid>https://imgur.com/a/bI2MvaE</guid><dc:creator><![CDATA[PresidentOfAntifa]]></dc:creator></item><item><title>The end and the beginning</title><link>https://imgur.com/gallery/KP1CyoW</link><description><![CDATA[<div><img alt="" src="https://i.imgur.com/kmQX65W.jpg" style="max-width: 90%; height: auto;"></div><div><span></span></div><div>This was my 15 year old puppy Mr Puckett</div><div><img alt="" src="https://i.imgur.com/kqEQXjZ.jpg" style="max-width: 90%; height: auto;"></div><div><span></span></div><div>He and I spent 12 years together, from sky rise condos in Seattle to homeless camps in Minneapolis and everywhere else inbetween</div><div><img alt="" src="https://i.imgur.com/ga9OZcO.jpg" style="max-width: 90%; height: auto;"></div><div><span></span></div><div>He was there with me through the worst of my addictions, the rock bottoms living on the street, and became a reason for me to fight to get better. 

After four years of homelessness we finally got back on our feet in 2019 and we moved to Tennessee to settle down.</div><div><img alt="" src="https://i.imgur.com/Q8HjRlD.jpg" style="max-width: 90%; height: auto;"></div><div><span></span></div><div>2 years ago today Mr Puckett passed away. 

It all happened so fast man, one month he was running 5ks and the next month he was gone. 

I didn't have a friend within 1,000 miles and I've never felt so lost in my life.</div><div><img alt="" src="https://i.imgur.com/jbj4wy7.jpg" style="max-width: 90%; height: auto;"></div><div><span></span></div><div>I promised him before he passed that I would never let his name die.

The next year I started Puckett Week as a digital charity event in his name. All I knew is that I wanted to help people get off the street like he did with me.</div><div><img alt="" src="https://i.imgur.com/Warhl4K.jpg" style="max-width: 90%; height: auto;"></div><div><span></span></div><div>I soon learned that the leading cause of homelessness for women and children in America is domestic violence. 

I ended up homeless due to my own decisions and consequences. I couldn't fathom women and children having to chose between abuse and going through what I did on the street.</div><div><img alt="" src="https://i.imgur.com/MHLRf5y.png" style="max-width: 90%; height: auto;"></div><div><span></span></div><div>This year in mainly $15 donations, the first two days of Puckett Week brought in over $7,000 for survivors of domestic violence facing homelessness, and over 100 items have been sent to them via an Amazon Wishlist</div><div><img alt="" src="https://i.imgur.com/5N5c2Uf.png" style="max-width: 90%; height: auto;"></div><div><span></span></div><div>Most people don't realize that this day is very special to me for another reason. 

I was so lost after Mr Puckett died, so close to relapse or self harm, I decided to go to an animal shelter just to be near other dogs.</div><div><img alt="" src="https://i.imgur.com/ot2MqqQ.gif" style="max-width: 90%; height: auto;"></div><div><span></span></div><div>3 hours after he died I took one lap around the shelter and found this beautiful dog. 

I had never even considered adopting again, but I knew I couldn't go home alone that night.</div><div><img alt="" src="https://i.imgur.com/mFnifs0.jpg" style="max-width: 90%; height: auto;"></div><div><span></span></div><div>MrsPuckett saved me that day, much in the same way Mr Puckett did for so many years.</div><div><img alt="" src="https://i.imgur.com/GA6hD0m.png" style="max-width: 90%; height: auto;"></div><div><span></span></div><div>She started running right away, and the more miles we put on the closer we grew. 

In the 2 years she's been home she's run 2 marathons, over 60 half marathons, and well over 3,000 miles total.</div><div><img alt="" src="https://i.imgur.com/RBIVc4F.jpg" style="max-width: 90%; height: auto;"></div><div><span></span></div><div>This is my best friend in the whole world.</div><div><img alt="" src="https://i.imgur.com/KY0z7rk.jpg" style="max-width: 90%; height: auto;"></div><div><span></span></div><div>Now I can look at February 18th as a day of growth rather than a day of remorse. 

As the incredible life of one dog came to an end, the start of an incredible life for another began.</div><div><img alt="" src="https://i.imgur.com/FMvkRAU.jpg" style="max-width: 90%; height: auto;"></div><div><span></span></div><div>With a little luck and a lot of work, hopefully these two will never have to know what it was like with Mr Puckett living on the street. 

With a little help and a lot of love, hopefully we can help abuse survivors get out of the shelter and into a safe home.

This is a pretty emotional week for me, and I wanted to thank everyone for being there for me.</div><div><img alt="" src="https://i.imgur.com/BmqZwAW.jpg" style="max-width: 90%; height: auto;"></div><div><span></span></div><div>The Mary Parrish Center provides free housing for survivors to leave their abusers and stay off the street. In Mr Puckett's honor, I'm asking anyone who can afford it to donate $15 to Mary Parrish and survivors -

https://www.maryparrish.org/donate

I also had them set up an Amazon Wishlist if you'd like to send items directly to their residents -

https://www.amazon.com/hz/wishlist/ls/3USHUHIVSINQE?ref_=wl_share

...

Thank you all again for being there for me, and being there for survivors. Mr Puckett may be gone, but I'll never stop trying to do good in his name.</div></div>]]></description><guid>https://imgur.com/a/KP1CyoW</guid><dc:creator><![CDATA[MrPuckett]]></dc:creator></item><item><title>The American Dream</title><link>https://imgur.com/gallery/1WlRYi9</link><description><![CDATA[<div><img alt="" src="https://i.imgur.com/1sb7pxr.png" style="max-width: 90%; height: auto;"></div><div><span></span></div></div>]]></description><guid>https://imgur.com/a/1WlRYi9</guid><dc:creator><![CDATA[prisonmike1991]]></dc:creator></item><item><title>Student Debt is a Scam</title><link>https://imgur.com/gallery/V1fn0of</link><description><![CDATA[<div><img alt="" src="https://i.imgur.com/qp6KXDc.jpg" style="max-width: 90%; height: auto;"></div><div><span></span></div></div>]]></description><guid>https://imgur.com/a/V1fn0of</guid><dc:creator><![CDATA[Smacketywack]]></dc:creator></item><item><title>Is Taco Bell the answer?</title><link>https://imgur.com/gallery/DGk1mMb</link><description><![CDATA[<div><img alt="" src="https://i.imgur.com/78N08lD.jpg" style="max-width: 90%; height: auto;"></div><div><span></span></div></div>]]></description><guid>https://imgur.com/a/DGk1mMb</guid><dc:creator><![CDATA[robdotwtf]]></dc:creator></item><item><title>Hmmmmmmm</title><link>https://imgur.com/gallery/REoEPy9</link><description><![CDATA[<div><img alt="" src="https://i.imgur.com/mvKdgBo.png" style="max-width: 90%; height: auto;"></div><div><span></span></div></div>]]></description><guid>https://imgur.com/a/REoEPy9</guid><dc:creator><![CDATA[SyedalTaker]]></dc:creator></item><item><title>What an honor</title><link>https://imgur.com/gallery/TwWVK3m</link><description><![CDATA[<div><img alt="" src="https://i.imgur.com/RQkSj6a.jpg" style="max-width: 90%; height: auto;"></div><div><span></span></div><div>I know imgur likes Betty White RIP</div></div>]]></description><guid>https://imgur.com/a/TwWVK3m</guid><d